>>> Your partition table suggests that there are two different partitions
>>> for
>>> '/boot'
>>> and '/'.  The GRUB loads the kernel from '/boot' which is (hd0,0) but
>>> the
>>> kernel is unable to find the '/' partition.   You may pass it using the
>>> parameter
>>> root=/dev/hda3.
>>>
>>> That should work.
>>>
>>> Prasad
